---
Kantianism:
  - Categorical Imperative (First Formulation):
    Act only from moral rules that you can at the same time will to be
    universal moral laws.
    
  - Categorical Imperative (Second Formulation):
    Act so that you always treat both yourself and other people as ends
    in themselves, and never only as a means to an end.

Social Contract Theory:
  - We all have social contract we have agreed to. Breaking these
    contracts are amoral.


Act Utilitarianism:
  - Perform Calculus of good vs bad using monetary value or something
    measurable.

Rule Utilitarianism:
  - We should adopt moral rule that lead to the greatest overall
    happines.
